00:20:08.745 --> 00:20:10.870
[LAUGHS]

00:20:10.870 --> 00:20:13.840
Does anyone have any exciting
questions about maintenance

00:20:13.840 --> 00:20:16.235
and your responsibilities
as a pilot?

00:20:16.235 --> 00:20:17.860
OK, there's a little
bit of interaction

00:20:17.860 --> 00:20:21.605
there between the
pilot and the mechanic.

00:20:21.605 --> 00:20:23.230
You can't practically
check everything.

00:20:23.230 --> 00:20:25.750
You have to rely
on mechanics, who

00:20:25.750 --> 00:20:27.470
are generally quite reliable.

00:20:27.470 --> 00:20:30.225
And they're FAA-certificated.

00:20:30.225 --> 00:20:31.600
But you have to
have a little bit

00:20:31.600 --> 00:20:35.530
of common sense about not
accepting a broken airplane

00:20:35.530 --> 00:20:36.445
or helicopter.

00:20:36.445 --> 00:20:37.070
Oh, [INAUDIBLE]

