00:22:01.948 --> 00:22:03.490
And then the other
thing I would just

00:22:03.490 --> 00:22:05.830
add to aircraft
ownership in general

00:22:05.830 --> 00:22:09.190
is that there are also a lot of
opportunities where there are--

00:22:09.190 --> 00:22:12.010
basically, you can become
part of a group that

00:22:12.010 --> 00:22:14.110
partially owns an airplane.

00:22:14.110 --> 00:22:17.110
So there's a bunch
of clubs around here

00:22:17.110 --> 00:22:19.990
where, for example, there
are three planes that

00:22:19.990 --> 00:22:22.630
are owned by 60 people.

00:22:22.630 --> 00:22:25.840
And so you kind of
timeshare those planes.

00:22:25.840 --> 00:22:28.870
And a number of the other
instructors of this course

00:22:28.870 --> 00:22:29.900
have done that.

00:22:29.900 --> 00:22:34.400
So you might have heard Luke
or Marissa talk about that.

00:22:34.400 --> 00:22:36.582
And so they have some
planes, for example,

00:22:36.582 --> 00:22:38.290
in Beverly, where
there are three planes,

00:22:38.290 --> 00:22:39.520
and a bunch of people own it.

00:22:39.520 --> 00:22:42.100
And so you can
timeshare the plane,

00:22:42.100 --> 00:22:45.610
and they have to be very
mindful about these types

00:22:45.610 --> 00:22:47.540
of maintenance aspects, as well.

00:22:47.540 --> 00:22:52.270
So it's kind of an in-between
cost of renting versus owning

00:22:52.270 --> 00:22:54.120
your own airplane by yourself.

00:22:54.120 --> 00:22:56.830
PHILIP GREENSPUN: Yeah,
